Title: CSS Isolation in ASP.NET Core 6.0
Description: This article will discuss about CSS Isolation in ASP.NET Core 6.0. CSS isolation simplifies an app’s CSS footprint by preventing dependencies on global styles and helps to avoid styling conflicts among components and libraries. CSS Isolation is enabled by default for ASP.NET Core 6.0 Projects. I am using Microsoft.AspNetCore.App 6.0.0-preview.3.21201.13 runtime in this project.
